1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 b6 4. g3 Ba6 {This is the main line and has become 
more popular than the natural-looking Bb7.} 5. Qb3 {This is one possible 
sideline.} Nc6 6. Nbd2 Na5 {The knight attacks the queen and prepares the 
advance of the c-pawn in the future.} 7. Qa4 Bb7 8. Bg2 c5 {Black strikes in the 
center.} 9. dxc5 bxc5 {Taking with the bishop is less common.} 10. O-O *

