[SourceTitle "01 Main Line"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "queens-indian-defense-tournament-edition/course/2358, variation/78951"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 b6 4. g3 Ba6 5. b3 {This is the most popular way of 
defending the c4-pawn.} Bb4+ 6. Bd2 Be7 7. Nc3 O-O {Black can simply castle.} 8. 
e4 d5 {It is very important that Black attacks White's center. Otherwise, he 
will simply get rolled over by White's pawns.} 9. cxd5 Bxf1 10. Kxf1 exd5 11. e5 
Ne4 {White should not take Black's knight because Black can recapture followed 
by a move such as Qd5, and White's d4 pawn suddenly becomes a target.} *

[Event "Queen's Indian Defense- Tournament Edition"]
[Site "Main Line"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
