[White "Main Line"]
[Black "?"]
[Result "*"]
[SourceTitle "01 Main Line"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "queens-indian-defense-tournament-edition/course/2358, variation/78952"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 b6 4. g3 Ba6 5. b3 Bb4+ 6. Bd2 Be7 7. Bg2 c6 {Black 
stops any threats that White's light-squared bishop might have on the h1-a8 
diagonal, while also preparing d7-d5.} 8. O-O d5 9. Ne5 Nfd7 {Black offers a 
trade of knights but is careful not to leave the c6 pawn unprotected.} 10. Nxd7 
Nxd7 11. Bc3 {The main move in this position.} O-O 12. Nd2 Rc8 13. e4 {White 
expands in the center.} b5 {c5 leads to a series of trades that will lead to a 
draw. If you are ok with a draw, then you should investigate that line and try 
it. I prefer playing for a win however with b5.} *

