1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 b6 4. g3 Ba6 5. b3 Bb4+ 6. Bd2 Be7 7. Bg2 c6 8. Bc3 d5 
9. Nbd2 Nbd7 10. O-O O-O 11. Re1 c5 {Black creates pawn tension in the center.} 
12. e4 dxe4 {This is one of the best moves in this position, but often leads to 
a series of trades.} 13. Nxe4 Bb7 14. Nfg5 cxd4 15. Bxd4 Qc7 16. Nxf6+ Bxf6 17. 
Bxb7 Qxb7 18. Ne4 {White can also simply take on f6 instead.} Bxd4 19. Qxd4 Rad8 
{The position is very balanced and is probably heading towards a draw, but Black 
certainly will not lose this position unless he plays the endgame horribly.} *

