nothing to worry about.} Bb7 6. Bg2 c5 7. O-O cxd4 8. Nxd4 Bxg2 9. Kxg2 Qc8 
{White's queen is not ideally placed on a4.} 10. Nc3 Be7 11. Rd1 O-O {Black can 
perhaps play d7-d5 in the future or develop his other knight. Overall, Black has 
a comfortable position.} *

