1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 b6 4. g3 Ba6 5. Qa4 Bb7 6. Bg2 c5 7. dxc5 {White may 
try taking immediately.} Bxc5 {This is my favorite way of recapturing the pawn, 
but bxc5 is also very playable.} 8. O-O O-O 9. Nc3 Be7 10. Rd1 Na6 11. Bf4 Nc5 
{Black's knight is nicely placed on the c5-square.} 12. Qc2 Qc8 13. Rac1 Nce4 
{Black has a good position. He will later put pressure on White's c-pawn or 
prepare a pawn break with d7-d5.} *

