White can play.} Be7 7. cxd5 Nxd5 {In this paricular line, Black gives up his 
pawn control of the e4 square. However, Black can later play c7-c5 and put 
pressure down the c-file with his rooks.} 8. e4 Nxc3 9. bxc3 O-O {Black should 
develop in away that facilitates an eventual c7-c5 pawn break to undermine 
White's center.} *

