1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 b6 4. a3 Bb7 5. Nc3 d5 6. cxd5 Nxd5 {Black does not 
have to recapture with the pawn because an immediate e2-e4 by White is not 
possible.} 7. e3 {e4 runs into Nxc3 followed by Bxe4, and Black wins a pawn.} g6 
{This is the latest trend.} 8. Bb5+ c6 9. Bd3 Bg7 10. O-O O-O 11. Na4 {White 
adds extra support to the c5-square and allows for b2-b4 in the future.} Nd7 12. 
e4 Ne7 {White has a big center, but Black will attack it relentlessly with pawn 
breaks such as c6-c5 or e6-e5.} *

