[SourceTitle "04 Spassky System"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "queens-indian-defense-tournament-edition/course/2358, variation/78914"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 b6 4. e3 {This is known as the Spassky System. It is a 
solid way to play, but it blocks in White's dark-squared bishop.} Bb7 {Black 
continues in standard fashion.} 5. Bd3 d5 6. O-O Bd6 {This is the best diagonal 
for Black's dark-squared bishop.} 7. Nc3 O-O 8. b3 Nbd7 9. Bb2 a6 {When the 
moment is right, Black will take on c4 to open up lines for his bishop on b7 and 
attack the center further with c7-c5.} *

