1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 b6 4. e3 Bb7 5. Nc3 {White can play this instead of 
Bd3 first, but it is less common.} Bb4 6. Bd3 O-O 7. O-O d5 {A Black needs to 
attack the center with his pawn at some point.} 8. cxd5 exd5 9. a3 Bd6 10. b4 a6 
{Controlling the b5-square.} 11. Qb3 Qe7 {White's play is directed at the 
queenside, while Black seeks to control the center without falling apart on the 
queenside.} *

