Nbd7 9. Nbd2 {White can also aim for this set-up instead of having the knight on 
c3.} Ne4 {A nice move, bringing the knight to a powerful square. White cannot 
make an effective trade on e4 because of the nasty forks that arise after a 
simple recapture with the pawn.} 10. Qc2 f5 {Black cements his knight on the 
excellent e5-square.} *

