1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 b6 4. Bf4 {This is a fairly uncommon sideline. You are 
most likely to see it at the amateur level, where many players do not know very 
much theory. It is a natural looking move, but it does not offer White anything 
special. Black equalizes easily.} Bb7 5. Nc3 {This is less common than e3.} Bb4 
6. Qb3 a5 7. e3 Ne4 {Black hits the pinned knight on c3.} *

